# .assetsignore — Cloudflare Workers static-assets ignore list (gitignore-style syntax).
# Adopted from clint-engine/templates/assetsignore (the canonical list — see
# clint-engine/docs/CONTRACTS.md "Templates & tools"). Keeps dev-only files, source control,
# and editable art masters out of the deployed bundle.
#
# engine/core and engine/dom (and engine/phaser, unused but harmless) DO ship — the game
# imports them at runtime. Nothing under engine/ needs excluding here.
#
# DEVIATION FROM THE CANONICAL TEMPLATE, found here (read code, not docs — MIGRATION_PLAN.md
# §"How later sessions use this file"): the template's bare `voice` line is NOT included below.
# Verified via js/voice.js: this game's "Read to me" quest narration fetches its Kokoro-TTS clips
# straight from assets/voice/quest_<id>.m4a at runtime (SRC = (id) => "assets/voice/quest_" + id
# + ".m4a") — that folder is shipped content, not a dev-only raw-recordings staging dir. Excluding
# it would silently break read-aloud in production. (Math Arcade's own .assetsignore hit and
# documented the same trap for its assets/audio/voice|vo/ clip banks.) The template's
# `art/img/*.png` line is also dropped — this game has no top-level art/ directory (its art lives
# under assets/art/, which is not excluded).

**/.wrangler
**/node_modules
**/.git
**/.DS_Store
**/.env
.claude
*.zip
*.md
wrangler.toml
.assetsignore
tools/
docs/

# Ctrl+Create-specific dev-only paths (see .gitignore for the same reasoning):
tmp/
tests/
